snippet.textDisplay: The joke was not calling kimchi disgusting (because obviously it isn’t disgusting and it tastes good) but more based on the fact that it tasted like a food in general. Kimchi was just a random food the writers probably picked. I get theres cultural differences and I understand how in Korean culture this may be deemed offensive, but in England sex is becoming less and less viewed as taboo or ‘gross’, and so the food in question isn’t linked to such connotations over here. Due to the cultural you do have a right to be offended and sorry if you were, but don’t start calling us Nazis and comparing us to people who literally murdered millions in the name of eugenics because of a mistake that was not intended to be racist.
